{
  "id": "infiniflow_ragflow_13217",
  "repo_name": "infiniflow/ragflow",
  "repo_url": "https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow",
  "base_commit": "2a5ddf064dc391dcb2f2edd2f386737a65790c6a",
  "pr_number": 13217,
  "issue_number": 13142,
  "issue_title": "[Feature Request]: API endpoints for auto-metadata configuration at dataset level",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\n```Markdown\nCurrently, the auto-metadata extraction feature is only configurable through the Web UI (Dataset > Configuration > Auto metadata > Settings).\nThere is no way to programmatically configure auto-metadata settings via HTTP API or Python SDK when creating or updating datasets.\n\nThis limitation prevents full automation of dataset creation workflows and makes it impossible to:\n- Programmatically define metadata fields with descriptions and examples\n- Enable/disable \"Restrict to defined values\" option via API\n- Create multiple datasets with different auto-metadata configurations without manual UI intervention\n- Integrate dataset creation with auto-metadata setup in CI/CD pipelines or infrastructure-as-code\n\nAdditionally, the current Web UI has bugs affecting list-type metadata fields that get reset to \"String\" type unexpectedly.\nHaving API access would allow users to work around these UI bugs by managing configurations programmatically with more reliability.\n```\n\n### Describe the feature you'd like\n\nAdd API support for configuring auto-metadata settings at the dataset level, including:\n\n1. **HTTP API endpoints:**\n   - Extend `POST /api/v1/datasets` to accept an optional `auto_metadata_config` parameter\n   - Add `PUT /api/v1/datasets/{dataset_id}/auto_metadata` for updating auto-metadata configuration\n   - Add `GET /api/v1/datasets/{dataset_id}/auto_metadata` to retrieve current configuration\n\n2. **Python SDK methods:**\n   - Add `auto_metadata_config` parameter to `rag.create_dataset()`\n   - Add `dataset.update_auto_metadata()` method\n   - Add `dataset.get_auto_metadata()` method\n\n**Proposed API structure:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"my_dataset\",\n  \"chunk_method\": \"generic\",\n  \"auto_metadata_config\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"fields\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"author\",\n        \"type\": \"string\",\n        \"description\": \"The author of the document\",\n        \"examples\": [\"John Doe\", \"Jane Smith\"],\n        \"restrict_values\": false\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"category\",\n        \"type\": \"list\",\n        \"description\": \"Document category\",\n        \"examples\": [\"Technical\", \"Business\", \"Legal\"],\n        \"restrict_values\": true\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"tags\",\n        \"type\": \"list\",\n        \"description\": \"Document tags\",\n        \"examples\": [\"AI\", \"ML\", \"RAG\"],\n        \"restrict_values\": false\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"year\",\n        \"type\": \"time\",\n        \"description\": \"Publication year\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\n### Describe implementation you've considered\n\nThis is a sample Python SDK implementation.\n\n# Create dataset with auto-metadata configuration\ndataset = rag.create_dataset(\n    name=\"my_dataset\",\n    chunk_method=\"naive\",\n    auto_metadata_config={\n        \"enabled\": True,\n        \"fields\": [\n            {\n                \"name\": \"author\",\n                \"type\": \"string\",\n                \"description\": \"Document author\",\n                \"examples\": [\"John\", \"Jane\"],\n                \"restrict_values\": False\n            },\n            {\n                \"name\": \"categories\",\n                \"type\": \"list\",\n                \"description\": \"Document categories\",\n                \"examples\": [\"Technical\", \"Business\"],\n                \"restrict_values\": True\n            }\n        ]\n    }\n)\n\n# Update existing dataset auto-metadata\ndataset.update_auto_metadata(\n    enabled=True,\n    fields=[...]\n)\n\n# Get current configuration\nconfig = dataset.get_auto_metadata()\n\n\n### Documentation, adoption, use case\n\n```Markdown\nUse cases:\n\t1.\tInfrastructure-as-Code: Define datasets with auto-metadata in configuration files for automated deployment\n\t2.\tMulti-tenant systems: Programmatically create datasets with different metadata schemas for different tenants/projects\n\t3.\tCI/CD pipelines: Automate dataset creation with standardized metadata extraction rules\n\t4.\tBatch operations: Create multiple datasets with similar auto-metadata configurations programmatically\n\t5.\tTemplate-based workflows: Replicate dataset configurations across environments (dev/staging/production)\n\t6.\tWorkaround for UI bugs: Reliably configure list-type metadata fields without experiencing the UI bug that resets them to string type\n\n\nImpact:\n\t\u2022\tEnables full automation of RAGFlow dataset management\n\t\u2022\tReduces manual configuration overhead for large-scale deployments\n\t\u2022\tImproves consistency across datasets with standardized metadata schemas\n\t\u2022\tFacilitates integration with external workflow orchestration tools\n\t\u2022\tProvides a stable alternative to the buggy UI for list-type metadata configuration\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\n**Current workaround:**\u2028Currently, users must manually configure auto-metadata through the Web UI for each dataset, which is not scalable for automated workflows or programmatic dataset management. Furthermore, the UI has known bugs where list-type metadata fields are incorrectly reset to string type, making it unreliable for certain configurations.\n\n**Priority**:\u2028This feature would significantly improve the developer experience for teams managing multiple datasets or deploying RAGFlow in automated environments. It would also provide a more reliable way to configure auto-metadata, bypassing the existing UI bugs.",
  "merged_at": "2026-02-26T02:25:48.000Z",
